Defendant Fredinard Jackson in court with attorney Christian Thomas Eichenlaub.  Abbey Marie DeSiato appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
cab
Amended Information received and filed changing the charge to 2 counts of Misdemeanor Battery, pursuant to Wisc. stats. 940.19(1).
As to both charges:
  Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.
Defense counsel waived reading of the Amended Information and entered a plea of not guilty on behalf of defendant.
.
Parties wish to proceed to sentencing...
.
As to counts 1 and 2:
  Statements by each counsel and defendant as to sentencing.  Court sentenced the defendant to serve 5 months in the House of Correction as to count 1 and 5 months in the House of Correctiona as to count 2, consecutive,   with credit for -0- days served.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed the defendant on probation for 16 months, concurrent,  with the following conditions:
- Serve 30 days in the House of Correction; STAYED.
- Complete a course in anger management.
- Attend treatment and/or counseling as determined.
- Any contact with the victim must coincide with any CHIPS order that is in effect.
- No contact with firearms.
- Pay DV surcharge plus all other costs and surcharges; civil judgment if not paid.
- Pay supervision fees.
